INSTALL — MY-cfg for Arch Linux + Hyprland
==================================================

This document provides a clean, copy‑pasteable, step‑by‑step guide to install the MY-cfg
(Hyprland + eww + wofi + kitty) configuration on Arch Linux.

Tested on: Arch Linux (Wayland). Assumes a fresh user profile with sudo rights.


0) Notes & backup
-----------------
• These commands install required packages, fonts, icons, and copy the repo’s configs into ~/.config.
• If you already have configs for hypr/eww/wofi/kitty, BACK THEM UP first:

  mkdir -p ~/backup-configs && \
  for d in hypr eww wofi kitty; do \
    [ -d "$HOME/.config/$d" ] && mv "$HOME/.config/$d" "$HOME/backup-configs/${d}-$(date +%F-%H%M%S)"; \
  done


1) Update system & base tools
-----------------------------
sudo pacman -Syu
sudo pacman -S --needed base-devel git curl


2) Install Hyprland stack and tools
-----------------------------------
# Hyprland compositor and useful Wayland utilities
sudo pacman -S --needed hyprland xdg-desktop-portal-hyprland wl-clipboard \
  hyprpaper hypridle swaybg grim slurp

# Polkit agent (choose ONE you prefer). Example: polkit-gnome
sudo pacman -S --needed polkit-gnome

# Optional but recommended for audio
sudo pacman -S --needed pipewire wireplumber pipewire-alsa pipewire-pulse pavucontrol


3) Install apps used by this config
-----------------------------------
# Terminal + app launcher
sudo pacman -S --needed kitty wofi

# AUR helper (yay) to install eww + Nerd Fonts
git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/yay.git
cd yay
makepkg -si
cd ..

# eww (widgets/panels)
yay -S --needed eww


4) Fonts & icon themes (to avoid missing glyphs)
------------------------------------------------
# Core text + emoji + CJK (optional but recommended for complete coverage)
sudo pacman -S --needed noto-fonts noto-fonts-emoji noto-fonts-cjk

# Icons and symbol fonts
sudo pacman -S --needed ttf-font-awesome papirus-icon-theme

# Nerd Fonts (commonly used by rice/configs). Install at least one full Nerd Font:
# (JetBrainsMono Nerd Font is a good default; add others if you wish)
yay -S --needed ttf-jetbrains-mono-nerd ttf-nerd-fonts-symbols ttf-nerd-fonts-symbols-mono


5) Clone MY-cfg and install configs
-----------------------------------
# Clone the repo (or update if you already have it)
git clone https://github.com/Gelepik/MY-cfg.git
cd MY-cfg

# Copy configs into ~/.config (create dirs if needed)
mkdir -p ~/.config
cp -r hypr ~/.config/
cp -r eww ~/.config/
cp -r wofi ~/.config/
cp -r kitty ~/.config/

# Ensure correct ownership/permissions (in case you copied as root by accident)
chown -R $USER:$USER ~/.config/hypr ~/.config/eww ~/.config/wofi ~/.config/kitty


6) Wallpaper, avatar, and name in eww
-------------------------------------
# Wallpaper:
# Put your wallpaper image into:  ~/Pictures/winda.jpg
# (Create the directory if it doesn’t exist)
mkdir -p ~/Pictures
# Example: if your image is /path/to/your_wallpaper.jpg
# cp /path/to/your_wallpaper.jpg ~/Pictures/winda.jpg

# Avatar (used by eww):
# Replace the file at:  ~/.config/eww/Monasm.jpg
# with your own image, but keep the exact same file name: Monasm.jpg

# Display name in the eww menu:
# Edit ~/.config/eww/eww.yuck, press Ctrl+F and find “Gelepa”, change it to your name.
# Example (using sed; make a backup first):
cp ~/.config/eww/eww.yuck ~/.config/eww/eww.yuck.bak 2>/dev/null || true
sed -i 's/Gelepa/YourNameHere/g' ~/.config/eww/eww.yuck


7) Startpage (browser home tab)
-------------------------------
# The repository includes: tartarus-startpage-master/index.html
# Option A: open it directly from the repo folder in your browser.
# Option B (recommended): copy it into a dedicated config location, then set your browser’s homepage to that file.
mkdir -p ~/.config/startpage
cp -f tartarus-startpage-master/index.html ~/.config/startpage/index.html

# Then set your browser’s homepage/start page to:
# file:///home/$USER/.config/startpage/index.html


8) Autostart eww and wallpaper in Hyprland
------------------------------------------
# In ~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf add (or ensure) lines like these in the 'exec-once' section:

# --- begin example ---
# Use hyprpaper for the wallpaper (uses the winda.jpg we placed earlier)
# Make sure ~/.config/hypr/hyprpaper.conf exists and points to your wallpaper:
#   preload = ~/Pictures/winda.jpg
#   wallpaper = ,~/Pictures/winda.jpg
# Then autostart hyprpaper and eww:
# exec-once = hyprpaper &
# exec-once = eww daemon && eww open <YOUR_WIDGET_NAME_IF_DEFINED>
# --- end example ---

# If your hypr config already contains exec-once lines, just add/merge these as needed.


9) First run
------------
# Log out to a TTY, log in and start Hyprland (if you don’t use a display manager):
Hyprland

# Or select Hyprland from your display manager (SDDM/GDM/etc.) session list.


10) Useful troubleshooting tips
-------------------------------
• If eww fails to launch, run it from a terminal to see errors:
  eww daemon
  eww open <widget_name>

• If you see missing icons/squares, ensure the fonts in step 4 are installed, then re-login.

• For wallpaper issues, verify ~/.config/hypr/hyprpaper.conf is valid and the image path exists.

• For portal issues (screensharing, file pickers), verify xdg-desktop-portal-hyprland is installed
  and no conflicting portal backends are running.


Appendix: One-liner quick install (expert use)
----------------------------------------------
# WARNING: modifies your configs, installs yay and lots of packages in one go.
# Read the steps above first, then run at your own risk.

sudo pacman -Syu --noconfirm && \
sudo pacman -S --needed --noconfirm base-devel git curl hyprland xdg-desktop-portal-hyprland \
  wl-clipboard hyprpaper hypridle swaybg grim slurp polkit-gnome pipewire wireplumber \
  pipewire-alsa pipewire-pulse pavucontrol kitty wofi noto-fonts noto-fonts-emoji \
  noto-fonts-cjk ttf-font-awesome papirus-icon-theme && \
git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/yay.git && cd yay && makepkg -si --noconfirm && cd .. && \
yay -S --needed --noconfirm eww ttf-jetbrains-mono-nerd ttf-nerd-fonts-symbols ttf-nerd-fonts-symbols-mono && \
git clone https://github.com/Gelepik/MY-cfg.git && cd MY-cfg && \
mkdir -p ~/.config && \
for d in hypr eww wofi kitty; do cp -r "$d" ~/.config/; done && \
mkdir -p ~/Pictures ~/.config/startpage && \
# Place your wallpaper at ~/Pictures/winda.jpg manually, then:
cp -f tartarus-startpage-master/index.html ~/.config/startpage/index.html && \
chown -R $USER:$USER ~/.config/hypr ~/.config/eww ~/.config/wofi ~/.config/kitty

# After this, edit ~/.config/eww/eww.yuck to change “Gelepa” to your name, replace Monasm.jpg,
# and configure hyprpaper/eww autostart inside ~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf.
